subject: New JUnit FAQ

messageBody:
The new JUnit FAQ is now available at:

http://junit.sourceforge.net/doc/faq/faq.htm

This file is also available in the SourceForge CVS repository and will
be distributed with upcoming JUnit releases.

Contributions are always appreciated. Simply write a frequently asked
question and answer, then blast me the text via private email. It's
easy! In fact, you're already doing the hard part by posting answers to
this mailing list. By contributing to the FAQ the knowledge you share
will be retained over time to help those new to the JUnit community for
years to come. As an added bonus, you hopefully won't have to wade
through the same repeated questions on this mailing list.

Many thanks to the contributors who's collective wisdom and effort made
this FAQ possible! Any errors or omissions are my fault.

Let me know if you have suggestions or corrections. I welcome any
feedback you may have.

Enjoy!

Mike
